---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Ancient Egypt — Pharaoh Terms That Score Big"
  description="Ancient Egypt words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. PHARAOH (15pts), SPHINX (18pts), OBELISK (13pts). Egyptian vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble egypt words, pharaoh scrabble points, sphinx scrabble, obelisk scrabble, ancient egypt terms scrabble, egyptian words scrabble, pyramid vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Ancient Egypt — Pharaoh Terms That Score Big","description":"Ancient Egypt words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. PHARAOH (15pts), SPHINX (18pts), OBELISK (13pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-ancient-egypt"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PHARAOH a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PHARAOH scores 15 points (P=3, H=4, A=1, R=1, A=1, O=1, H=4) in Scrabble. It uses two H tiles (H=4 each) for 8 points from those alone. Refers to an ancient Egyptian ruler. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play SPHINX in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. SPHINX scores 18 points (S=1, P=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, X=8) as a 6-letter word. The X=8 and H=4 combine for 12 points from just two tiles, making it a devastating play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is OBELISK valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! OBELISK scores 13 points (O=1, B=3, E=1, L=1, I=1, S=1, K=5) as a 7-letter bingo candidate. With the 50-point bonus, it's worth 63 points. The K=5 and B=3 provide the value."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Ancient Egypt — Pharaoh Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Ancient Egypt's legacy extends beyond pyramids and mummies — it provides a treasure trove of Scrabble words. Egyptian terminology is packed with H tiles, X tiles, K tiles, and P tiles that turn your rack into a pharaoh's ransom of points.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SPHINX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PHARAOH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">OBELISK</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PAPYRUS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Egyptian Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">SPHINX — 18 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">S=1, P=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, X=8 · 6 letters · X-tile powerhouse</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The mythical creature with a lion's body and human head. SPHINX scores 18 points from 6 tiles with X=8 and H=4 doing the heavy lifting. At 3.0 points per tile, it's one of the most efficient X-word plays available.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👑 PHARAOH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · P=3, H=4, A=1, R=1, A=1, O=1, H=4 · Double H</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🗿 OBELISK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · O=1, B=3, E=1, L=1, I=1, S=1, K=5 · Bingo candidate</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏛️ PYRAMID</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · P=3, Y=4, R=1, A=1, M=3, I=1, D=2 · Ancient tomb</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📜 PAPYRUS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · P=3, A=1, P=3, Y=4, R=1, U=1, S=1 · Writing material</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Egyptian Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>Ancient Egyptian culture lends many words to English that score well in Scrabble:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SCARAB</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANKH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TOMB</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MUMMY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DYNASTY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Egyptian Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SPHINX maximises X + H:</span> X=8 and H=4 together account for 12 of the 18 points. SPHINX is easier to play than many X words because S, P, I, N are all common tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PHARAOH uses both H tiles:</span> With H=4 appearing twice, PHARAOH (15pts) earns 8 points from H alone. If you draw both H tiles, this 7-letter word is a bingo candidate worth 65 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OBELISK is an accessible bingo:</span> At 7 letters with K=5 and B=3, OBELISK (13pts + 50 bonus = 63pts) uses common tiles. The word is well-known, making it easy to spot on your rack.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Egyptian words are <span class="text-white font-medium">H-tile and X-tile specialists</span>. SPHINX uses X+H for 12 points from two tiles, PHARAOH leverages double H=4, and ANKH pairs K+H. When you draw H tiles (especially with X, K, or P), think ancient Egypt — this vocabulary makes premium tiles shine.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-egyptian/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Egyptian Mythology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-ancient-rome/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Ancient Rome</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-archaeology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Archaeology</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid Egyptian word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
